This paper focuses on the development of an autonomous system for AUV mission planning and path planning in a highly uncertain and dynamic environment. The use of evolutionary algorithms for control and optimization suggests a focus on robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The consideration of system constraints and real-time performance suggests a focus on systems and control (cs.SY) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the use of metaheuristic algorithms suggests a focus on mathematical optimization (cs.MA).
